parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle snaps off
the female end of the buckle does not receive the male part
the red button on the buckle is broken
the plastic seat belt buckle splits
allowing the seat belt to slip out of the buckle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the starter motor can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The starter motor only works intermittently
the starter motor requires banging or tapping to function
the vehicle fails to start
the starter motor makes a clicking sound but fails to engage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Mounting Failure and Fire Risk
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery mounting system can cause the battery to fall into the engine compartment, leading to a fire risk, which can result in damage to the vehicle, injury, or even loss of life.
symptoms: The battery falls into the engine compartment
the battery tray or shelf fails
the vehicle catches on fire
the engine compartment is damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. It can also result in costly repairs and downtime.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies
the engine makes unusual noises
the engine overheats
the engine warning light comes on
the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine head cylinder failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to further damage and potentially causing the engine to seize or fail. This can result in costly repairs and downtime.
symptoms: The engine overheats
the engine makes unusual noises
the engine warning light comes on
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
coolant leaks from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate tightening of the fuel filter nut can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents, potentially resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
fuel smell
fuel dripping from the fuel filter area
difficulty starting the engine
engine stalling
decreased engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator pedal cable can cause the pedal to stick, leading to unintended acceleration, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal feels stuck or stuck in a position
the engine revs high and will not return to normal
the vehicle surges or accelerates unexpectedly.
